'''Gani Bobi''' ([[Serbian Cyrillic]]: Гани Боби) (20 November 1943 – 17 July 1995) was an [[Albanians|Albanian]] [[philosopher]] and [[sociologist]] from [[Kosovo]]{{ref label|status|a|}}. He was born in Lubenić, municipality of [[Peć]], [[Democratic Federal Yugoslavia]]. He was one of the first Albanian professors of sociology and philosophy at the [[University of Pristina (1969–1999)|University of Pristina]] (1981).<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Fnbw1wsacSAC&pg=PA27&dq=Gani+Bobi&lr=#v=onepage&q=Gani%20Bobi&f=false Historical dictionary of Kosova ''By Robert Elsie'', page 27]</ref> He got a doctorate degree in sociology at the [[University of Belgrade]] [[University of Belgrade Faculty of Philosophy|Faculty of Philosophy]] in 1986 after finishing his studies in language and literature at the University of Pristina. He lived in [[Pristina]]. His publications have been published in five volumes called ''Vepra''. Among his main publications were ''Sprovimet e modernitetit'' (1982), ''Paradoks kulturor'' (1986) and ''Konteksti i vetëkulturës'' (1994), some of them translated into English and Serbian.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?d=Fnbw1wsacSAC&pg=PA27&dq=Gani+Bobi&lr=#v=onepage&q=Gani%20Bobi&f=false Historical dictionary of Kosova ''By Robert Elsie'', page 27]</ref>

''Gani Bobi Center'' for Social Studies founded by [[Shkëlzen Maliqi]] was named after him.<ref>[http://ganibobi.com/gani_bobi_presentation.pdf Gani Bobi Center]</ref>

During his later days he worked as editor of philosophy at ''Koha'' magazine published in Pristina in 1994.<ref>''KOHA Ditore 10 vjetët e parë'', Koha Prishtinë 2007, pg. 173 ([ftp://82.114.77.27/pub/shtojcat-monografia/monografia_kohaditore.pdf  english])</ref>

